HEADWORD: Commingler
<hw>Com*min"gler</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One that
commingles; specif., a device for noiseless heating of water by steam,
in a vessel filled with a porous mass, as of pebbles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

